TITLE: COUNT Query with TYPO3 Query Builder
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating and executing a COUNT query to get the number of records matching specific criteria.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Database\Connection;

// SELECT COUNT(`uid`) FROM `tt_content` WHERE (`bodytext` = 'lorem')
//     AND ((`tt_content`.`deleted` = 0) AND (`tt_content`.`hidden` = 0)
//     AND (`tt_content`.`starttime` <= 1669885410)
//     AND ((`tt_content`.`endtime` = 0) OR (`tt_content`.`endtime` > 1669885410)))
$queryBuilder = $this->connectionPool->getQueryBuilderForTable('tt_content');
$count = $queryBuilder
    ->count('uid')
    ->from('tt_content')
    ->where(
        $queryBuilder->expr()->eq('bodytext', $queryBuilder->createNamedParameter('lorem', Connection::PARAM_STR))
    )
    ->executeQuery()
    ->fetchOne();
```

