TITLE: Protecting Against SQL Injection with createNamedParameter() in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the importance of using createNamedParameter() to protect against SQL injection when dealing with user input in database queries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
// SELECT * FROM `tt_content` WHERE (`bodytext` = 'kl\'aus')
$searchWord = "kl'aus"; // $searchWord retrieved from the PSR-7 request
$queryBuilder = $this->connectionPool->getQueryBuilderForTable('tt_content');
$queryBuilder->getRestrictions()->removeAll();
$queryBuilder
    ->select('uid')
    ->from('tt_content')
    ->where(
        $queryBuilder->expr()->eq(
            'bodytext',
            $queryBuilder->createNamedParameter($searchWord, Connection::PARAM_STR)
        )
    )
    ->executeQuery();
```

