TITLE: Using Interface Injection in TYPO3 Extension Service
DESCRIPTION: A PHP class demonstrating how to use dependency injection with the PSR-20 clock interface in a TYPO3 extension service, allowing for better testability by injecting the interface rather than a concrete implementation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/DependencyInjection/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Service;

use Psr\Clock\ClockInterface;

final readonly class MyService
{
    public function __construct(
        private ClockInterface $clock,
    ) {
    }

    public function doSomething(): \DateTimeImmutable
    {
        // Use the injected clock interface
        return $this->clock->now();
    }
}
```

