TITLE: Sending Email with MailMessage in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create and send an email using the MailMessage class, including setting recipients, subject, and both text and HTML content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Mail/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Symfony\Component\Mime\Address;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Mail\MailMessage;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Utility\GeneralUtility;

// Create the message
$mail = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(MailMessage::class);

// Prepare and send the message
$mail
    // Defining the "From" email address and name as an object
    // (email clients will display the name)
    ->from(new Address('john.doe@example.org', 'John Doe'))

    // Set the "To" addresses
    ->to(
        new Address('receiver@example.org', 'Max Mustermann'),
        new Address('other@example.org')
    )

    // Give the message a subject
    ->subject('Your subject')

    // Give it the text message
    ->text('Here is the message itself')

    // And optionally an HTML message
    ->html('<p>Here is the message itself</p>')

    // Optionally add any attachments
    ->attachFromPath('/path/to/my-document.pdf')

    // And finally send it
    ->send()
;
```

