TITLE: Using Method-Level PHP Attributes for TYPO3 Event Listeners
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use PHP attributes at the method level to define multiple event listeners within a single class in TYPO3.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/EventDispatcher/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php
namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Attribute\AsEventListener;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Mail\Event\BeforeMailerSentMessageEvent;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Mail\Event\AfterMailerSentMessageEvent;

final class MailerEventListener
{
    #[AsEventListener(
        identifier: 'my-extension/before-mailer-sent'
    )]
    public function beforeMailerSent(BeforeMailerSentMessageEvent $event): void
    {
        // Before mailer sent logic
    }

    #[AsEventListener(
        identifier: 'my-extension/after-mailer-sent'
    )]
    public function afterMailerSent(AfterMailerSentMessageEvent $event): void
