TITLE: Configuring Redis Caching Backend in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: Example configuration for setting up the Redis caching backend in TYPO3. This code shows how to configure different caches with separate Redis databases to prevent key collisions between cache types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/CachingFramework/FrontendsBackends/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
// Define names for caches that should go into own redis databases
// this array maps cache identifiers to database numbers
$redisCaches = [
    // frontend caches
    'pages' => 1,
    'pagesection' => 2,
    'rootline' => 3,
    'hash' => 4,
    // core internal caches
    'extbase' => 10,
    'fluid_template' => 11,
];
// Add redistribution config for registered caches
$GLOBALS['TYPO3_CONF_VARS']['SYS']['caching']['cacheConfigurations'] = array_map(
    function ($cacheName) use ($redisCaches) {
        $conf = $GLOBALS['TYPO3_CONF_VARS']['SYS']['caching']['cacheConfigurations'][$cacheName] ?? [];
        if (isset($redisCaches[$cacheName])) {
            if (!isset($conf['backend'])) {
                $conf['backend'] = \TYPO3\CMS\Core\Cache\Backend\RedisBackend::class;
            }
            if (!isset($conf['options'])) {
                $conf['options'] = [];
            }
            $conf['options']['database'] = $redisCaches[$cacheName];
        }
        return $conf;
    },
    array_keys($GLOBALS['TYPO3_CONF_VARS']['SYS']['caching']['cacheConfigurations'])
);

```

