TITLE: Using union and addUnion in TYPO3 Query Builder (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the union and addUnion methods to combine result sets from multiple queries. The example demonstrates creating a UNION query with two subqueries on the tt_content table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Database/QueryBuilder/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// Prepare the connection and main query builder
$connection = $this->connectionPool->getConnectionForTable('tt_content');
$queryBuilder = $connection->createQueryBuilder();

// Prepare sub-query builders
$queryBuilder1 = $connection->createQueryBuilder();
$queryBuilder2 = $connection->createQueryBuilder();
$expr = $queryBuilder->expr();

// Build the UNION query
$result = $queryBuilder
    ->union(
        $queryBuilder1
            ->select('uid', 'pid', 'header')
            ->from('tt_content')
            ->where($expr->eq('CType', $queryBuilder->createNamedParameter('text')))
    )
    ->addUnion(
        $queryBuilder2
            ->select('uid', 'pid', 'header')
            ->from('tt_content')
            ->where($expr->eq('CType', $queryBuilder->createNamedParameter('textpic')))
    )
    ->orderBy('uid')
    ->executeQuery()
    ->fetchAllAssociative();
```

