TITLE: Implementing RecordAccessGrantedEvent Event Listener in TYPO3 CMS
DESCRIPTION: An example implementation of an event listener for the RecordAccessGrantedEvent in TYPO3 CMS. This listener can be used to control access to records or modify records before access is evaluated.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Core/Domain/RecordAccessGrantedEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Domain\Access;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Domain\Access\RecordAccessGrantedEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(RecordAccessGrantedEvent $event): void
    {
        // Called once for each record access check
        // You can:
        // * Modify the record via $event->getRecord() and $event->setRecord()
        // * Skip regular access check and always grant access via $event->setAccessGranted(true)
        // * Skip regular access check and always deny access via $event->setAccessGranted(false)

        // Example: Always grant access to records with specific title
        $record = $event->getRecord();
        if (($record['title'] ?? '') === 'Public Record') {
            $event->setAccessGranted(true);
        }

        // Example: Modify a record before access is checked
        if ($event->getTable() === 'pages') {
            $record = $event->getRecord();
            // Add some information
            $record['modified_by_event'] = true;
            $event->setRecord($record);
        }
    }
}
```

