TITLE: Implementing a Container in FormEngine Rendering for TYPO3 CMS in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Example of a container class implementation for the FormEngine rendering process. It demonstrates how to initialize a result array, fetch sub-container results via NodeFactory, and merge child results with the container's own output.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/FormEngine/Rendering/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Containers;

use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\Form\Container\AbstractContainer;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Utility\GeneralUtility;
use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\Form\NodeFactory;

class SomeContainer extends AbstractContainer
{
    public function render(): array
    {
        $result = $this->initializeResultArray();

        // Get some variable from data array that was prepared by FormDataCompiler
        $someData = $this->data['someData'];

        // Calculate something
        $someLabel = 'foobar';

        // Prepare the container HTML and set it in the result
        $result['html'] = '<div class="someFancyClass">' . htmlspecialchars($someLabel) . '</div>';

        // Create an instance of NodeFactory to resolve a sub-container or element
        $nodeFactory = GeneralUtility::makeInstance(NodeFactory::class);

        // Hand over data array to sub container, just add renderType = subContainer here, so the registry
        // in NodeFactory can find the class responsible for this renderType.
        $this->data['renderType'] = 'subContainer';

        // Call sub-container, get result back, this calls render() on our sub container or element
        $childArray = $nodeFactory->create($this->data)->render();

        // Add sub-container HTML at specific position in HTML
        $result['html'] = str_replace('###CHILD_HTML###', $childArray['html'], $result['html']);

        // Merge additional sub-container results like required JavaScript and CSS
        $result = $this->mergeChildReturnIntoExistingResult($result, $childArray);

        return $result;
    }
}
```

