TITLE: Implementing ModifyRedirectManagementControllerViewDataEvent Event Listener in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: Example implementation of an event listener for the ModifyRedirectManagementControllerViewDataEvent that modifies the view data by adding custom information to page records. This demonstrates how to use this PSR-14 event to extend the redirect management interface.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Redirects/ModifyRedirectManagementControllerViewDataEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Redirects\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Redirects\Event\ModifyRedirectManagementControllerViewDataEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(ModifyRedirectManagementControllerViewDataEvent $event): void
    {
        // Get the current view data
        $viewData = $event->getViewData();

        // Get the currently shown page records from the view data
        $demand = $viewData['demand'] ?? null;
        $paginator = $viewData['paginator'] ?? null;
        $pages = $viewData['pages'] ?? [];

        // Only proceed if we have valid data
        if ($demand !== null && $paginator !== null && !empty($pages)) {
            // Modify page records. As an example, add dummy data
            foreach ($pages as $identifier => $page) {
                $pages[$identifier]['customData'] = 'My custom data for ' . $page['target'] ?? '';
            }

            // Set modified pages back to view data
            $viewData['pages'] = $pages;

            // Update the view data
            $event->setViewData($viewData);
        }
    }
}
```

