TITLE: URI Builder in Another Context
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to inject the URI builder into a class using constructor injection. It highlights the importance of setting the request object before using the URI builder. The PSR-7 request object is retrieved from the global variable `TYPO3_REQUEST` in this example.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ExtensionArchitecture/Extbase/Reference/UriBuilder.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
"<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\\MyExtension\\Domain\\Model;

use Psr\\Http\\Message\\ServerRequestInterface;
use TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Http\\Uri;
use TYPO3\\CMS\\Extbase\\Mvc\\Web\\Routing\\UriBuilder;

class MyClass
{
    /**
     * @var UriBuilder
     */
    protected UriBuilder $uriBuilder;

    /**
     * @param UriBuilder $uriBuilder
     */
    public function __construct(
        UriBuilder $uriBuilder
    ) {
        $this->uriBuilder = $uriBuilder;
        $this->uriBuilder->setRequest($GLOBALS['TYPO3_REQUEST']);
    }

    /**
     * @return string
     */
    public function doSomething(): string
    {
        $uri = $this->uriBuilder
            ->reset()
            ->setTarget('show')
            ->setArguments(['foo' => 'bar'])
            ->setControllerName('My')
            ->setExtensionName('MyExtension')
            ->setPluginName('Pi1')
            ->build();

        return (string)$uri;
    }
}
"
```

