DESCRIPTION: Example of how to add ES6 modules to the current page response using either PageRenderer or JavaScriptRenderer in a TYPO3 backend environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Backend/JavaScript/ES6/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Vendor\MyExtension;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Page\JavaScriptModuleInstruction;

// Add module @vendor/my-extension/my-module to current response
$this->pageRenderer->loadJavaScriptModule('@vendor/my-extension/my-module.js');

// alternatively via JavaScriptRenderer
$this->pageRenderer->getJavaScriptRenderer()
    ->addJavaScriptModuleInstruction(
        JavaScriptModuleInstruction::create('@vendor/my-extension/my-module.js')
            // passing attributes
            ->instance(['key' => 'value'])
            // invoke method of instance
            ->invoke('method', ['argument1', 'argument2'])
            // invoke static method
            ->invokeStaticMethod('method', ['argument1', 'argument2'])
);

```

