TITLE: Implementing Custom Error Handler Class in PHP for TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: This PHP class implements the PageErrorHandlerInterface for a custom 404 error handler in TYPO3. It includes a constructor for initialization and a handlePageError method that generates an HTML response with the error details.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/SiteHandling/ErrorHandling/WriteCustomErrorHandler.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
namespace MyVendor\MySitePackage\Error;

use Psr\Http\Message\ResponseInterface;
use Psr\Http\Message\ServerRequestInterface;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Error\PageErrorHandler\PageErrorHandlerInterface;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Http\HtmlResponse;

class MyErrorHandler implements PageErrorHandlerInterface
{
    protected int $statusCode;
    protected array $configuration;

    public function __construct(int $statusCode, array $configuration)
    {
        $this->statusCode = $statusCode;
        $this->configuration = $configuration;
    }

    public function handlePageError(
        ServerRequestInterface $request,
        string $message,
        array $reasons = []
    ): ResponseInterface {
        $html = '<html><body>';
        $html .= '<h1>Page not found</h1>';
        $html .= '<p>' . htmlspecialchars($message) . '</p>';
        $html .= '</body></html>';

        return new HtmlResponse($html, $this->statusCode);
    }
}
```

