TITLE: Using AfterFileCreatedEvent in TYPO3 Core API
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the PSR-14 AfterFileCreatedEvent class, which is fired after a file is created in TYPO3. It provides access to the created file, storage, and folder objects, allowing for post-creation modifications or validations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Core/Resource/AfterFileCreatedEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
final class AfterFileCreatedEvent
{
    private File $file;
    private ResourceStorage $storage;
    private Folder $folder;

    public function __construct(File $file, ResourceStorage $storage, Folder $folder)
    {
        $this->file = $file;
        $this->storage = $storage;
        $this->folder = $folder;
    }

    public function getFile(): File
    {
        return $this->file;
    }

    public function getStorage(): ResourceStorage
    {
        return $this->storage;
    }

    public function getFolder(): Folder
    {
        return $this->folder;
    }
}
```

