TITLE: Implementing a Custom Event Listener for PackageInitializationEvent in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create a custom event listener that reacts to package initialization events. The listener demonstrates how to access extension key information, check for specific extensions, and store custom data in the event.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Core/Package/PackageInitializationEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Package\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Attribute\AsEventListener;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Package\Event\PackageInitializationEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    #[AsEventListener(
        identifier: 'my-extension/package-initialization',
    )]
    public function __invoke(PackageInitializationEvent $event): void
    {
        // Get the extension key
        $packageKey = $event->getPackageKey();

        // Demonstrate event storage usage
        if ($packageKey === 'my_custom_extension') {
            $storageData = $event->getStorageEntry('core.database') ?? [];
            // Do something with the storage data
            $event->addStorageEntry('my_extension.custom_data', ['foo' => 'bar']);
        }
    }
}

```

