TITLE: Implementing Page Tree Sorting with AfterRawPageRowPreparedEvent in TYPO3 CMS PHP
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create an event listener that sorts pages by title in the TYPO3 page tree. The listener implements the AfterRawPageRowPreparedEvent to modify how pages are ordered when displayed in the backend.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Backend/AfterRawPageRowPreparedEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Backend\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\Tree\Repository\AfterRawPageRowPreparedEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(AfterRawPageRowPreparedEvent $event): void
    {
        $pageRow = $event->getPageRow();
        $children = $event->getChildren();

        // Sort children by title
        if (!empty($children)) {
            usort($children, static function (array $a, array $b): int {
                return strnatcasecmp($a['title'], $b['title']);
            });
            $event->setChildren($children);
        }
    }
}
```

