TITLE: Adding JavaScript Modules in FormEngine Container for TYPO3 CMS in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add JavaScript ES6 modules to a FormEngine container. This is the recommended way to add JavaScript resources, as it works correctly with both standard and Ajax rendering contexts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/FormEngine/Rendering/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Backend;

use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\Form\Container\AbstractContainer;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Page\JavaScriptModuleInstruction;

class SomeContainer extends AbstractContainer
{
    public function render(): array
    {
        $resultArray = $this->initializeResultArray();

        $resultArray['html'] = 'My HTML code';

        // Add a JavaScript ES6 module to the result array
        $resultArray['javaScriptModules'][] = JavaScriptModuleInstruction::create(
            '@myvendor/my-extension/my-module'
        );

        // Or with additional arguments
        $resultArray['javaScriptModules'][] = JavaScriptModuleInstruction::create(
            '@myvendor/my-extension/my-module-with-arguments'
        )->instance(['foo' => 'bar']);

        return $resultArray;
    }
}
```

