TITLE: Handling Requests in TYPO3 Backend Controller
DESCRIPTION: PHP implementation of the handleRequest method in a backend controller. This method serves as the main entry point for the module, determining which action to execute based on the request and returning the rendered HTML response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ExtensionArchitecture/HowTo/BackendModule/CreateModule.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
/**
 * Main entry method for the controller.
 */
public function handleRequest(ServerRequestInterface $request): ResponseInterface
{
    $this->initializeModuleTemplate($request);

    $actionName = $request->getQueryParams()['action'] ?? $request->getParsedBody()['action'] ?? 'debug';

    $result = '';
    switch ($actionName) {
        case 'debug':
            $result = $this->debugAction($request);
            break;
    }

    $this->view->setContent($result);

    return new HtmlResponse($this->view->render());
}
```

