TITLE: Fetching and Loading File Collections in a TYPO3 Controller
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to retrieve file collections using the FileCollectionRepository and load their contents. It handles retrieving collections by UID or retrieving all collections, then iterates through them calling loadContents() to populate the files before passing them to the view.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Fal/Collections/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Controller;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Resource\FileCollectionRepository;
use TYPO3\CMS\Extbase\Mvc\Controller\ActionController;

class MyController extends ActionController
{
    /**
     * @var FileCollectionRepository
     */
    protected $collectionRepository;

    /**
     * Inject the file collection repository
     *
     * @param FileCollectionRepository $collectionRepository
     */
    public function injectFileCollectionRepository(FileCollectionRepository $collectionRepository)
    {
        $this->collectionRepository = $collectionRepository;
    }

    /**
     * List action
     */
    public function listAction()
    {
        // Get all collections
        $collections = $this->collectionRepository->findAll();
        // Or get a specific collection
        // $collections = [$this->collectionRepository->findByUid(1)];

        // Don't forget to load the contents for each collection
        foreach ($collections as $collection) {
            $collection->loadContents();
        }

        $this->view->assign('collections', $collections);
    }
}
```

