TITLE: Using ExpressionBuilder::right() in TYPO3 Repository (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the usage of the right() function in a TYPO3 repository to extract characters from the right side of a string. It demonstrates creating a SELECT statement that includes the rightmost characters of a field.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Database/ExpressionBuilder/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
public function findRightValues(): array
{
    $queryBuilder = $this->connectionPool->getQueryBuilderForTable('my_table');
    $queryBuilder
        ->select('uid')
        ->addSelect(
            $queryBuilder->expr()->right(
                'some_field',
                5
            ),
            'right_value'
        )
        ->from('my_table');

    return $queryBuilder->executeQuery()->fetchAllAssociative();
}
```

