TITLE: Implementing BeforeModuleCreationEvent Listener in TYPO3 CMS
DESCRIPTION: Example implementation of an event listener that manipulates module configuration before module creation in TYPO3 CMS backend. This listener handles the PSR-14 BeforeModuleCreationEvent.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Backend/BeforeModuleCreationEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declared(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Backend\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\Module\BeforeModuleCreationEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(BeforeModuleCreationEvent $event): void
    {
        // Access configuration
        $configuration = $event->getConfiguration();

        // Modify configuration
        $configuration['labels']['title'] = 'My custom module title';
        $configuration['access'] = 'user';

        // Set modified configuration
        $event->setConfiguration($configuration);
    }
}
```

