TITLE: Defining SwitchUserEvent Class in PHP for TYPO3 CMS
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines the SwitchUserEvent class in the TYPO3 CMS backend authentication namespace. It includes properties for the original and target user, as well as methods to get and set these users.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Backend/SwitchUserEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
final class SwitchUserEvent
{
    private BackendUserAuthentication $originalUser;
    private BackendUserAuthentication $targetUser;

    public function __construct(BackendUserAuthentication $originalUser, BackendUserAuthentication $targetUser)
    {
        $this->originalUser = $originalUser;
        $this->targetUser = $targetUser;
    }

    public function getOriginalUser(): BackendUserAuthentication
    {
        return $this->originalUser;
    }

    public function getTargetUser(): BackendUserAuthentication
    {
        return $this->targetUser;
    }

    public function setTargetUser(BackendUserAuthentication $targetUser): void
    {
        $this->targetUser = $targetUser;
    }
}
```

