TITLE: Implementing a BeforeRecordLanguageOverlayEvent Listener in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create an event listener that changes the overlay type to "on" (connected) for records. This approach helps when dealing with a site configured with free mode, but having record types with connected languages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Core/Domain/BeforeRecordLanguageOverlayEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Domain\Language;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Context\LanguageAspect;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Domain\Event\BeforeRecordLanguageOverlayEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(BeforeRecordLanguageOverlayEvent $event): void
    {
        $tableName = $event->getTableName();
        $record = $event->getRecord();
        $languageAspect = $event->getLanguageAspect();

        if ($tableName === 'tt_content' && $record['CType'] === 'myCoolExtension_mytype') {
            // Set overlay mode to "on" (connected) for all languages for this CType
            $event->setLanguageAspect(
                new LanguageAspect(
                    $languageAspect->getId(),
                    $languageAspect->getContentId(),
                    0 // overlayType = 0 means "connected"/"on"
                )
            );
        }
    }
}
```

