TITLE: Implementing JavaScript for Custom Field Control in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code defines the behavior for the custom field control in TYPO3. It sets up an event listener for the import button and sends an Ajax request to import data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/FormEngine/Rendering/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
define(['jquery', 'TYPO3/CMS/Backend/Notification'],
    function ($, Notification) {
        'use strict';

        $(document).on('click', '.importData', function (evt) {
            evt.preventDefault();
            var $anchorElement = $(this);
            var id = $anchorElement.data('id');

            $.ajax({
                url: TYPO3.settings.ajaxUrls['record_import'],
                data: {
                    id: id
                }
            }).done(function (response) {
                if (response.success) {
                    Notification.success('Success', 'Data imported');
                } else {
                    Notification.error('Error', 'Could not import data');
                }
            });
        });
    }
);
```

