TITLE: Implementing BeforeFinalSearchQueryIsExecutedEvent Listener in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: Example event listener implementation that demonstrates how to manipulate the QueryBuilder instance before the final search query is executed. This code would be placed in a TYPO3 extension under the specified path.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/IndexedSearch/BeforeFinalSearchQueryIsExecutedEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\IndexedSearch\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Database\Query\QueryBuilder;
use TYPO3\CMS\IndexedSearch\Event\BeforeFinalSearchQueryIsExecutedEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(BeforeFinalSearchQueryIsExecutedEvent $event): void
    {
        $queryBuilder = $event->getQueryBuilder();

        // Modify the query builder object
        // Note: The query builder API is not considered public API
        // and might change between TYPO3 versions
        $queryBuilder->andWhere(
            $queryBuilder->expr()->eq('item_type', $queryBuilder->createNamedParameter('0'))
        );
    }
}
```

