TITLE: Importing Routes into Site Configuration using SiteConfigurationLoadedEvent in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates an event listener that adds a route enhancer configuration to the site configuration automatically. It checks if the configuration already exists and adds it if not present.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Core/Configuration/SiteConfigurationLoadedEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Configuration\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Configuration\Event\SiteConfigurationLoadedEvent;

final class ImportRoutesIntoSiteConfiguration
{
    public function __invoke(SiteConfigurationLoadedEvent $event): void
    {
        $configuration = $event->getConfiguration();

        if (!isset($configuration['routeEnhancers']['MyPlugin'])) {
            $configuration['routeEnhancers']['MyPlugin'] = [
                'type' => 'Plugin',
                'limitToPages' => [
                    // Extend or replace with your page uid
                    1,
                ],
                'namespace' => 'tx_myplugin',
                'routePath' => '/my-plugin/{article_title}',
                'aspects' => [
                    'article_title' => [
                        'type' => 'PersistedSlugifiedPatternMapper',
                        'tableName' => 'tx_myplugin_domain_model_article',
                        'routeFieldPattern' => '^(?P<path_segment>.+)$',
                        'routeFieldResult' => '{path_segment}',
                    ],
                ],
            ];

            $event->setConfiguration($configuration);
        }
    }
}

```

