TITLE: Using EnrichFileMetaDataEvent in TYPO3 CMS
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the EnrichFileMetaDataEvent class from the TYPO3 Core Resource component. The event is triggered after file metadata has been loaded from the database and allows for runtime modification of the metadata.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Core/Resource/EnrichFileMetaDataEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace TYPO3\CMS\Core\Resource\Event;

/**
 * This event is fired after a record has been loaded from database.
 *
 * Listeners to this event could perform additional tasks and/or
 * modify/extend the metadata array.
 *
 * Example: Translation and workspace overlay.
 */
final class EnrichFileMetaDataEvent
{
    private array $metaDataProperties;
    private int $fileUid;
    private string $tableName;

    public function __construct(array $metaDataProperties, int $fileUid, string $tableName)
    {
        $this->metaDataProperties = $metaDataProperties;
        $this->fileUid = $fileUid;
        $this->tableName = $tableName;
    }

    public function getMetaDataProperties(): array
    {
        return $this->metaDataProperties;
    }

    public function setMetaDataProperties(array $metaDataProperties): void
    {
        $this->metaDataProperties = $metaDataProperties;
    }

    public function getFileUid(): int
    {
        return $this->fileUid;
    }

    public function getTableName(): string
    {
        return $this->tableName;
    }
}

```

