TITLE: Using BeforePageLanguageOverlayEvent in TYPO3 CMS
DESCRIPTION: The BeforePageLanguageOverlayEvent is fired when TYPO3 is about to perform language overlay operations on page records. It allows modification of page records before the language overlay is applied.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Core/Domain/BeforePageLanguageOverlayEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
final class BeforePageLanguageOverlayEvent
{
    /**
     * A list of (already preprocessed) language overlay items, indexed by uid.
     * These records can be modified, but adding or removing keys from the records array is not supported.
     * @var array<int, array<string, mixed>>
     */
    private array $records;

    /**
     * @param array<int, array<string, mixed>> $records
     */
    public function __construct(array $records)
    {
        $this->records = $records;
    }

    /**
     * @return array<int, array<string, mixed>>
     */
    public function getRecords(): array
    {
        return $this->records;
    }

    /**
     * @param array<int, array<string, mixed>> $records
     */
    public function setRecords(array $records): void
    {
        $this->records = $records;
    }
}
```

