TITLE: Registering Cache Tags in Extbase Controller with CacheDataCollector
DESCRIPTION: Example of how to add cache tags to the current page rendering using the CacheDataCollector in an Extbase controller. This ensures the page cache is automatically cleared when specific records are updated in the backend.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/DataHandler/Database/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Controller;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Cache\CacheDataCollector;

class SomeController extends \TYPO3\CMS\Extbase\Mvc\Controller\ActionController
{
    public function detailAction(\MyVendor\MyExtension\Domain\Model\Entity $entity): \Psr\Http\Message\ResponseInterface
    {
        // Get CacheDataCollector from request attribute
        $cacheDataCollector = $this->request->getAttribute('frontend.cache.collector');
        if ($cacheDataCollector instanceof CacheDataCollector) {
            // Register a tag for the specific record
            $cacheDataCollector->addCacheTags(['tx_myextension_entity_' . $entity->getUid()]);
        }

        $this->view->assign('entity', $entity);
        return $this->htmlResponse();
    }
}
```

