TITLE: Using ModifyLanguagePacksEvent in TYPO3 (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to implement an event listener for the ModifyLanguagePacksEvent in TYPO3. The event allows customizing which extensions or language packs should be ignored during the language pack download process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Install/ModifyLanguagePacksEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Install\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Install\Service\Event\ModifyLanguagePacksEvent;

/**
 * Modify which extensions / language packs should be downloaded from languages.typo3.org
 */
final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(ModifyLanguagePacksEvent $event): void
    {
        $event->setExtensionIsIgnored('news', true);

        // A typical use-case is to ignore all extension language packs
        // that are shipped together with an extension
        foreach ($event->getExtensionKeys() as $extensionKey) {
            // Example:
            if ($extensionKey === 'acme_demo') {
                // Ignore languages packs for acme_demo extension
                $event->setExtensionIsIgnored($extensionKey, true);
            }

            if ($extensionKey === 'fluid_styled_content') {
                // Ignore Dutch language pack for fluid_styled_content
                $event->setLanguagePackIsIgnored($extensionKey, 'nl', true);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

