TITLE: Implementing a Listener for AfterFormDefinitionLoadedEvent in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: Example implementation of an event listener that modifies a form definition after it has been loaded. This demonstrates how to register a listener using PHP attributes and modify form properties based on specific conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Form/AfterLinkResolvedByStringRepresentationEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Form\Mvc\Persistence\Event\AfterFormDefinitionLoadedEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(AfterFormDefinitionLoadedEvent $event): void
    {
        $persistenceIdentifier = $event->getPersistenceIdentifier();
        $formDefinition = $event->getFormDefinition();

        // Only handle a specific form
        if ($persistenceIdentifier !== 'EXT:my_extension/Resources/Forms/MyForm.yaml') {
            return;
        }

        // Add additional fields
        if (isset($formDefinition['renderables'][0]['renderables'])) {
            $formDefinition['renderables'][0]['renderables'][] = [
                'identifier' => 'additionalField',
                'type' => 'Text',
                'label' => 'This field has been added via AfterFormDefinitionLoadedEvent',
            ];
        }

        $event->setFormDefinition($formDefinition);
    }
}
```

