TITLE: Basic BitSet Usage Example in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic usage of the TYPO3 BitSet class with global constants to handle boolean flags.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/BitSets/Index.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

define('FLAG_NONE', 0b000);
define('FLAG_ONE', 0b001);
define('FLAG_TWO', 0b010);
define('FLAG_THREE', 0b100);

$bitSet = new \TYPO3\CMS\Core\Type\BitSet(FLAG_NONE);

// Set some flags
$bitSet->set(FLAG_ONE | FLAG_THREE);

// Test if flags are set
$bitSet->get(FLAG_ONE); // true
$bitSet->get(FLAG_TWO); // false
$bitSet->get(FLAG_THREE); // true

// Remove a flag
$bitSet->remove(FLAG_THREE);
$bitSet->get(FLAG_THREE); // false
```

