TITLE: Implementing a ModifyValidatorTaskEmailEvent Listener in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to implement an event listener for the ModifyValidatorTaskEmailEvent in TYPO3. The listener modifies the FluidEmail object to set custom email recipients and assigns additional template variables based on the linkvalidator task results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Linkvalidator/ModifyValidatorTaskEmailEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types = 1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Linkvalidator\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Mail\FluidEmail;
use TYPO3\CMS\Linkvalidator\Event\ModifyValidatorTaskEmailEvent;
use TYPO3\CMS\Linkvalidator\Result\LinkAnalyzerResult;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(ModifyValidatorTaskEmailEvent $event): void
    {
        $modTsConfig = $event->getModTSconfig();
        $fluidEmail = $event->getFluidEmail();
        $linkAnalyzerResult = $event->getLinkAnalyzerResult();

        $fluidEmail
            ->to('admin@example.org')
            ->assign('customData', [
                'customKey' => 'customValue'
            ]);

        $this->addCustomLinkData($linkAnalyzerResult);
    }

    protected function addCustomLinkData(LinkAnalyzerResult $linkAnalyzerResult): void
    {
        $brokenLinks = $linkAnalyzerResult->getBrokenLinks();

        foreach ($brokenLinks as &$brokenLink) {
            // Add custom data for each broken link
            $brokenLink['custom_data'] = [
                'date' => new \DateTime(),
            ];
        }

        $linkAnalyzerResult->setBrokenLinks($brokenLinks);
    }
}
```

