TITLE: Implementing a BeforePagePreviewUriGeneratedEvent Listener in TYPO3
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to implement an event listener for the BeforePagePreviewUriGeneratedEvent to modify the page preview URI generation process. The listener can adjust parameters like page ID and language ID or set a custom preview URI.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Backend/BeforePagePreviewUriGeneratedEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Backend\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\Routing\Event\BeforePagePreviewUriGeneratedEvent;

final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(BeforePagePreviewUriGeneratedEvent $event): void
    {
        // Set a complete custom URI, which will stop the event propagation and also
        // prevents TYPO3\CMS\Backend\Routing\PreviewUriBuilder from building the
        // Preview URI on its own.
        // $event->setPreviewUri('https://example.org');

        // Or change one or multiple parameter which will be used for building
        // the preview URI.
        $event->setPageId(123);
        $event->setLanguageId(2);
        $event->setSection('c123');
        $event->setType(1551338925);
        $event->setRootLine([['uid' => 123, 'pid' => 0]]);
        $event->setParameters(['foo' => 'bar']);
        $event->setAdditionalQueryParameters(['baz' => 'bar']);
    }
}
```

