TITLE: Extending Page Tree Search Filter in TYPO3 CMS (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create an event listener class that adds additional conditions to the page tree filter in TYPO3 CMS. It evaluates document types as part of the search filter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Backend/BeforePageTreeIsFilteredEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1)

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Backend\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\Tree\Repository\BeforePageTreeIsFilteredEvent;
use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Attribute\AsEventListener;

#[AsEventListener]
final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(BeforePageTreeIsFilteredEvent $event): void
    {
        $queryBuilder = $event->getQueryBuilder();
        $expr = $queryBuilder->expr();

        $searchParts = $event->getSearchParts();
        $searchPhrase = $event->getSearchPhrase();

        // Add search for specific document types
        $documentTypes = ['article', 'blog', 'news'];
        if (in_array($searchPhrase, $documentTypes, true)) {
            $searchParts[] = $expr->eq('doktype', 1);
            $searchParts[] = $expr->eq('backend_layout', $searchPhrase);
        }

        $event->setSearchParts($searchParts);
    }
}
```

