TITLE: Custom Event Listener with Custom Source Implementation (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows a custom event listener that removes the default PlainSlugReplacementSource and adds a custom source implementation. It demonstrates how to manipulate the sources for which redirects should be created.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Redirects/SlugRedirectChangeItemCreatedEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Redirects\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Attribute\AsEventListener;
use TYPO3\CMS\Redirects\Event\SlugRedirectChangeItemCreatedEvent;
use TYPO3\CMS\Redirects\RedirectUpdate\PlainSlugReplacementSource;
use MyVendor\MyExtension\Redirects\CustomSource;

#[AsEventListener(
    identifier: 'my-extension/manage-redirect-sources'
)]
final class MyEventListener
{
    public function __invoke(SlugRedirectChangeItemCreatedEvent $event): void
    {
        $sources = $event->getSources();
        foreach ($sources as $key => $source) {
            if ($source instanceof PlainSlugReplacementSource) {
                unset($sources[$key]);
            }
        }
        $event->setSources($sources);
        $event->addSource(new CustomSource());
    }
}
```

