TITLE: Implementing Sudo Mode Authentication Service in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to implement a custom authentication service for sudo mode in TYPO3 extensions. It shows how to intercept valid login requests instead of all authUser invocations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Backend/BackendModules/SudoMode.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Authentication;

use TYPO3\CMS\Core\Authentication\AbstractAuthenticationService;

class MyAuthenticationService extends AbstractAuthenticationService
{
    public function authUser(array $user): int
    {
        if (!$this->isActualLoginRequest()) {
            // skip auth chain for non-login requests (e.g. sudo mode)
            return self::STATUS_AUTHENTICATION_SUCCESS_BREAK;
        }
        // proceed with custom authentication
        return $this->customAuthenticationLogic($user);
    }

    protected function isActualLoginRequest(): bool
    {
        return ($this->authInfo['loginType'] === 'BE'
            && $this->login['status'] === 'login'
            && !empty($this->login['uident'])
        );
    }

    protected function customAuthenticationLogic(array $user): int
    {
        // custom authentication logic
    }
}
```

