TITLE: Manipulating Download Presets Event Listener in TYPO3 CMS
DESCRIPTION: Example implementation of an event listener that modifies download presets for specific database tables in TYPO3's Web > List module. It adds a custom preset for the 'pages' table and modifies existing presets for the 'tt_content' table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/Events/Events/Backend/BeforeRecordDownloadPresetsAreDisplayedEvent.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace MyVendor\MyExtension\Backend\EventListener;

use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\RecordList\DownloadPreset;
use TYPO3\CMS\Backend\RecordList\Event\BeforeRecordDownloadPresetsAreDisplayedEvent;

final readonly class PresetListener
{
    public function __invoke(BeforeRecordDownloadPresetsAreDisplayedEvent $event): void
    {
        // Add a preset to pages tables
        if ($event->getTable() === 'pages') {
            $presets = $event->getPresets();
            $presets['LLL:EXT:my_extension/Resources/Private/Language/locallang.xlf:export.title'] =
                new DownloadPreset(
                    label: 'LLL:EXT:my_extension/Resources/Private/Language/locallang.xlf:export.title',
                    columns: ['title', 'slug', 'sys_language_uid']
                );
            $event->setPresets($presets);
        }

        // Modify existing presets for content elements
        if ($event->getTable() === 'tt_content') {
            $presets = $event->getPresets();
            // Add a new column to download preset for standard preset
            $existingStandardPreset = $presets['standard'] ?? null;
            if ($existingStandardPreset instanceof DownloadPreset) {
                $columns = $existingStandardPreset->getColumns();
                // Add sys_language_uid
                $columns[] = 'sys_language_uid';
                $presets['standard'] = new DownloadPreset(
                    label: $existingStandardPreset->getLabel(),
                    columns: $columns
                );
            }
            // Remove extended preset
            unset($presets['extended']);
            $event->setPresets($presets);
        }
    }
}
```

