TITLE: Handling Arguments and Options in Command Execution
DESCRIPTION: Example of retrieving command arguments and options in the execute() method using InputInterface methods getArgument() and getOption().
SOURCE: https://github.com/TYPO3-Documentation/TYPO3CMS-Reference-CoreApi/blob/main/Documentation/ApiOverview/CommandControllers/Tutorial.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
/**
 * Executes the command
 */
protected function execute(InputInterface $input, OutputInterface $output): int
{
    $io = new SymfonyStyle($input, $output);
    $wizardName = $input->getArgument('wizardName');
    $isBoring = $input->getOption('boring');

    if ($wizardName) {
        $io->writeln('Wizard name is: ' . $wizardName);
    } else {
        $io->writeln('No wizard name provided');
    }

    if ($isBoring) {
        $io->writeln('This is a boring wizard');
    } else {
        $io->writeln('This is a fancy wizard');
    }

    return Command::SUCCESS;
}
```

